    {# ── CSAT ── #}
    <h2 class="section-heading" id="csat">CSAT — Paper 2 (Qualifying)</h2>
    <div class="pr-stats" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-4);">
      <div class="pr-stat"><span class="pr-stat__num">80</span><span class="pr-stat__label">Questions</span></div>
      <div class="pr-stat"><span class="pr-stat__num">200</span><span class="pr-stat__label">Marks</span></div>
      <div class="pr-stat"><span class="pr-stat__num">2 hrs</span><span class="pr-stat__label">Duration</span></div>
      <div class="pr-stat"><span class="pr-stat__num">33%</span><span class="pr-stat__label">Qualifying (66/200)</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="pr-csat">
      <div class="pr-csat-card"><h4>Comprehension</h4><p>Largest section. Answers are always within the passage — don't use outside knowledge. Practice reading speed.</p></div>
      <div class="pr-csat-card"><h4>Logical Reasoning</h4><p>Syllogisms, sequences, Venn diagrams, blood relations, direction sense. Pattern-based — most scoring section.</p></div>
      <div class="pr-csat-card"><h4>Basic Numeracy</h4><p>Class 10 math: percentages, ratios, averages, time-speed-distance. No calculator. Practice mental math.</p></div>
      <div class="pr-csat-card"><h4>Data Interpretation</h4><p>Bar charts, pie charts, tables. Approximate — don't calculate exactly. Read data carefully.</p></div>
      <div class="pr-csat-card"><h4>Decision Making</h4><p>Administrative scenarios. Choose balanced, ethical, practical options. Avoid extreme positions.</p></div>
    </div>

